#help on making git work with Rstudio 
from bash
git config --global user.name "your_username"
git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"
ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "your_email@example.com" 
ssh -T git@github.com
git config remote.origin.url git@github.com:your_username/your_project.git


this is from 
http://applyr.blogspot.com.eg/2014/05/rstudio-pushing-to-github-with-ssh.html

my terminal is : /usr/bin/lxterminal

this is also useful
https://www.datascienceriot.com/how-to-link-r-studio-to-your-github-account/kris/


I used the email elmahy2005@gmail.com
and the user.name ahmedelmahy

I did it for subsequent projects

in the case of  Permission denied (publickey).
copy the root/.ssh/Just copy your /root/.ssh/id_rsa.pub content as new github SSH key